9) Switches facilitate communications WITHIN  a network. They are a combination of Hubs(7) and Bridges(8).
   - Switches act like a hub, where they are able to send traffic from any port to any other port. 
   - Switches are alos like a bridge, where they can learn where to send the traffic. Meaning, they are able to destinguish 
between certain traffic.
   - Unlike Bridges, Switches have multiple ports.

