10) Routers facilitate communications BETWEEN different networks. 
    - Routers are what allow your devices to communicate other networks.
    - Since the internet is one huge network, routers are what enable communication with the internet.
    - Routers provide a traffic control point. They secure, filter and redirect traffic. 
    - They are the first line of defense against cyber attacks.
    - Routers are a bottleneck for traffic. It is logical to apply security policies to the router. Hence, first line of 
defense.
    - Traditionally, switches could not perform filtering - However, some modern switches are able to do so.
    - Routers have their own IP Address, which allows their hosts to exit the network. Meaning, the Routers IP Address is 
the Gateway for the individual hosts. (Shown in 11)

